<h2>Mousetrap Adapter</h2>
<p>
    The Mousetrap Adapter connects the <a href="https://craig.is/killing/mice">Mousetrap</a> library to Web Everything's <strong>Keyboard Shortcuts Module</strong>. It lets an app keep Mousetrap's familiar binding syntax while its shortcuts flow through the standard's registry.
</p>

<section class="section-card fui-card">
    <h3 id="status">Status</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
        <strong>Implemented.</strong> The bridge ships in the <a href="https://github.com/">Frontier UI</a> reference implementation
        (<code>adapters/mousetrap-keyboard-shortcuts/mousetrapAdapter.ts</code>) with a full unit-test suite. Per the WE
        zero-implementation rule the module <em>contract</em> is defined here; the bridge <em>code</em> is impl.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="section-card fui-card">
    <h3 id="concept">How it works</h3>
    <p>
        Mousetrap is a popular library for handling keyboard shortcuts. The adapter is <strong>dependency-free by
        construction</strong>: it never pins or installs Mousetrap. Instead the caller passes a Mousetrap-shaped instance
        (anything with <code>bind</code>/<code>unbind</code>/<code>reset</code>), and the adapter maps the module's neutral
        <code>ShortcutBinding</code> shape onto it:
    </p>

    {% highlight "typescript" %}
import { bridgeMousetrap } from '@frontierui/adapters/mousetrap-keyboard-shortcuts';
import Mousetrap from 'mousetrap'; // the caller owns the dependency

// Register shortcuts through the Keyboard Shortcuts Module's neutral shape.
const shortcuts = bridgeMousetrap(Mousetrap, [
  { keys: 'mod+s',        handler: () => save() },
  { keys: 'mod+shift+s',  handler: () => saveAs() },
  { keys: ['esc'],        handler: () => closeDialog(), on: 'keyup' },
]);

// The returned handle is live — add / remove / dispose re-drive Mousetrap.
shortcuts.add({ keys: 'up up down down', handler: () => konami() });
shortcuts.remove('mod+shift+s');
shortcuts.dispose(); // unbinds everything this registration bound
    {% endhighlight %}

    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
        Chords are normalised to Mousetrap's spelling (<code>mod+s</code>, case-insensitive modifiers); space-separated
        combos stay <strong>sequences</strong> (e.g. <code>up up down down</code>). All keyboard mechanics remain in
        Mousetrap — the adapter is a thin, deterministic mapping.
    </p>
</section>

